claim.claim-text:
1. A transistor comprising: 
an intrinsic silicon body having a first surface; 
a gate dielectric on said first surface of said intrinsic silicon body; 
a gate electrode formed on said gate dielectric, said gate electrode comprising a mid-gap work function film on said gate dielectric; and 
a pair of source/drain regions on opposite sides of said intrinsic silicon body.

12. A method of forming a transistor comprising: 
forming an intrinsic silicon film having a first surface on an insulating substrate; 
forming a gate dielectric layer on said first surface of said intrinsic silicon body; 
forming a gate electrode on said gate dielectric, wherein said gate electrode comprises a mid-gap work function film on said gate dielectric; and 
forming a pair of source/drain regions on opposite sides of said intrinsic silicon body.

21. A transistor comprising: 
an intrinsic silicon body having a first surface and a thickness less than 500A formed on an insulating substrate; 
a gate dielectric on said first surface of said intrinsic silicon body; 
a gate electrode formed on said gate dielectric, said gate electrode comprising a mid-gap work function film on said gate dielectric and a doped polysilicon film on said mid-gap work function film; 
a pair of sidewall spacers adjacent to opposite sides of said gate electrode; and 
a pair of source/drain regions on opposite sides of said intrinsic silicon body, said pair of source/drain regions each comprising: 
ultra shallow tip region beneath said sidewall spacers and said gate electrode and adjacent to said intrinsic silicon body; 
a raised tip region adjacent to said sidewall spacers and said ultra shallow tip region, said raised tip region comprising an epitaxial silicon or silicon alloy film formed above said first surface; and 
a contact region comprising an epitaxial silicon or silicon alloy film above said first surface and adjacent to said raised tip region.
